vulnerabilities.name: CVE-2016-10539
vulnerabilities.description: negotiator is an HTTP content negotiator for Node.js and is used by many modules and frameworks including Express and Koa. The header for "Accept-Language", when parsed by negotiator 0.6.0 and earlier is vulnerable to Regular Expression Denial of Service via a specially crafted string.

topFix.fixResolution:
Upgrade to at least version 0.6.1

Express users should update to Express 4.14.0 or greater. If you want to see if you are using a vulnerable call,  a quick grep for the `acceptsLanguages` function call in your application will tell you if you are using this functionality.
